The paper presents algorithms for point-set cover and pattern discovery, which are common topics in computer science. The use of TECs and translators suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the evaluation on the JKU Patterns Development Database suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The use of compression factor and recall/precision metrics suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and the potential use of coding theory suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT).
